[Name] Ion
[Summary] A tiling tabbed window manager designed with keyboard users in mind.
[License] GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL)
[Description] Ion is a tiling (no overlapping windows) window manager that also has PWM-style tabbed frames which can contain multiple client windows. These features help to keep windows organized and to switch quickly between them. Ion was designed primarily as an efficient and unobtrusive window manager for users who prefer the keyboard.
[Homepage] http://iki.fi/tuomov/ion/
